Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithmic aspects of determining the prime factor decomposition of directed graphs with respect to the strong product, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The construction of the Cartesian skeleton is a key component of the algorithm, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) in terms of the complexity analysis of the algorithm. The sub-category of distributed systems (cs.DS) is less likely as the paper does not explicitly deal with distributed systems.
